<h2>Copyright Law</h2>
<p>
<img src="images/02_04_handcuff.gif" alt="Handcuffs" width="76" height="72" border="0" align="right">
Legally, only the copyright holder has the right to or grant permission to: 

</p>
<ol>
<li>
make copies of the work (this means digital copies too)
</li>
<li>
create derivative work, or collect money from derivative work (this means that legally, you cannot base a work on an existing copyrighted work without permission)
</li>
<li>
distribute copies of the work (this means digital copies too)
</li>
<li>
perform the work in public
</li>
<li>
display the work in public 
</li>
</ol>
<p class="citation">
<a href="JavaScript:Citation('0017');">17 USC 106, 2002</a>
</p> 
